com.ibm.team.process.common.advice.runtime

Interface IOperationAdviceListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    OperationAdviceListener

    public interface IOperationAdviceListener
    Listener interface for notification about changes to the advice model.

    Since notification is synchronous with the execution of operations, the listener should provide a fast-running implementation. If the handling of notifications would involve blocking operations, the notifications should be queued and the actual processing deferred (or perhaps delegated to a separate thread).

    A default implementation of this interface, OperationAdviceListener, is available for clients to extend if they do not wish to implement all methods.

    Since:
    0.5
